metadata.title: the inca portal
metadata.user_prompt: The story of Coco a young kid in Peru visiting El Museo de La nacion with his classmates and then getting transported to the Inca times after touching a Inca artifact that turned out to be a time portal. He has to find the portal again to come back.

pages.text: Era una vez un niño llamado Coco que vivía en Perú. Coco era curioso, ingenioso y siempre lleno de energía. Un día, él y sus compañeros de clase se preparaban para una visita muy especial: El Museo de la Nación en Lima. Coco estaba emocionado, ya que siempre había soñado con aprender más sobre los Incas, una antigua civilización que una vez reinó en su país.

Cuando llegaron al museo, Coco y sus amigos quedaron asombrados por las grandes salas llenas de artefactos antiguos, pinturas coloridas y estatuas majestuosas. La profesora los llevó a una sala donde se exhibían numerosos artefactos de los Incas. Coco no podía quitar sus ojos de una joya brillante que parecía muy antigua. Su curiosidad se despertó.

Coco extendió la mano y tocó la joya. De repente, se sintió mareado y todo a su alrededor comenzó a girar. Cuando abrió los ojos, se encontró de pie en un valle exuberante, con montañas tan altas que parecían tocar el cielo. Coco se dio cuenta de que ya no estaba en el museo, sino en los tiempos de los Incas.

Todo parecía tan real: las personas vestidas con ropas coloridas, las casas de piedra y los campos de maíz que se extendían hasta donde alcanzaba la vista. Coco se encontró con un niño de su edad llamado Kusi, quien, al darse cuenta de la confusión de Coco, le explicó que había viajado a través de un portal de tiempo.

Aunque Coco estaba asombrado y encantado con todo lo que veía, sabía que tenía que encontrar el camino de regreso a su tiempo. Kusi, siendo amable y servicial, decidió ayudar a Coco. Juntos, emprendieron una búsqueda para encontrar el portal de tiempo.

En su viaje, Coco aprendió sobre la vida de los Incas, su idioma quechua, cómo cultivaban su comida y cómo construían sus casas. Se sorprendió de cuán avanzados eran y de cuánto respetaban la naturaleza. Pero a pesar de toda la diversión, Coco no podía dejar de pensar en su hogar y en sus amigos.

Finalmente, después de viajar por montañas y valles, llegaron a un antiguo templo. Kusi explicó que este era el lugar donde Coco había llegado, el portal de tiempo. Coco se acercó y vio la misma joya que había tocado en el museo.
Sintiéndose un poco asustado, Coco extendió la mano y tocó la joya. Al igual que antes, todo a su alrededor comenzó a girar. Cuando abrió los ojos, se encontró en el museo, frente a la misma joya.

Coco se quedó allí, asombrado, mientras sus compañeros de clase y su profesora se acercaban. ¿Había sido todo un sueño? Pero entonces, notó que todavía tenía en su bolsillo una pequeña piedra que Kusi le había dado como recuerdo.

Aunque Coco volvió a su tiempo y a su vida normal, su aventura con los Incas fue algo que nunca olvidaría. Cada vez que miraba la piedra, recordaba a Kusi, el valle exuberante, las montañas y todo lo que había aprendido. Coco no solo había hecho un viaje a través del tiempo, sino que también había hecho un viaje de descubrimiento y aprendizaje.

characters.name: Coco
characters.physical_description: Coco is a 10-year-old boy with a medium build and average height for his age. He has dark brown skin, expressive dark eyes, and short, curly black hair. His face is round with a small nose and a wide, bright smile. His arms and legs are slightly skinny, reflecting his active nature.
characters.clothing: Coco wears a vibrant red t-shirt with a simple design of a llama, a pair of denim shorts that reach his knees, and sturdy brown sandals suitable for his adventures. He also has a small, blue backpack where he keeps his essentials.
characters.distinctive_features: Coco's most distinctive feature is a small, round birthmark on his left cheek. He also has a noticeable gap between his front teeth that becomes visible when he smiles.
characters.personality_traits: Coco's curiosity and energy are evident in his wide, bright eyes and the way he carries himself with an eager posture. His ingenious nature is reflected in the thoughtful expression he often wears, especially when he is exploring or learning something new.

characters.name: Sus compañeros de clase
characters.physical_description: Coco's classmates are a diverse group of children aged around 10 years old. They vary in height, but none are taller than 5 feet. They have different skin tones ranging from light to dark, and their hair colors vary from black, brown, to blonde. Some have curly hair, others have straight or wavy hair. They have bright, curious eyes of different colors - brown, blue, green, and hazel.
characters.clothing: They are all dressed in school uniforms. The boys wear navy blue trousers and white shirts, and the girls wear navy blue skirts and white blouses. They all wear black shoes and white socks. Some of them have accessories like hair bands, glasses, and wristwatches.
characters.distinctive_features: Each classmate has a unique feature. One boy has freckles, one girl has braces, another boy wears glasses, and another girl has her hair in braids. These features make each of them distinctive and recognizable.
characters.personality_traits: Their expressions show a range of personalities. Some look curious and eager, some look shy and reserved, and others look mischievous and playful. These traits are reflected in their body language and facial expressions.

characters.name: La profesora
characters.physical_description: La profesora is a middle-aged woman of average height and build. She has dark brown hair that she wears in a neat bun at the back of her head. Her skin is a warm tan color, and she has brown eyes that sparkle with intelligence and kindness. She wears glasses with round, gold-rimmed frames.
characters.clothing: She wears a traditional Andean blouse in bright colors, paired with a long, dark skirt. On her feet, she wears comfortable, brown leather shoes suitable for walking. She also wears a long, gold chain necklace with a pendant in the shape of an Inca sun god.
characters.distinctive_features: Her distinctive features include her glasses, her bun hairstyle, and her Inca sun god pendant. She always carries a large, leather-bound book about Peruvian history.
characters.personality_traits: La profesora's personality traits are visible in her warm smile and the attentive look in her eyes. She is intelligent, kind, and has a deep love for teaching and history. Her clothing and accessories reflect her pride in her Peruvian heritage.

characters.name: Los Incas
characters.physical_description: Coco is a young boy of average height and build for his age. He has dark, wavy hair that falls just above his eyebrows. His skin is a warm, medium brown, and his eyes are a bright, curious black. Kusi, the Inca boy, is about the same age and height as Coco, but has straight, black hair that is cut short. His skin is a deeper shade of brown, and his eyes are a dark, intelligent brown.
characters.clothing: Coco wears modern clothing: a red t-shirt, blue jeans, and white sneakers. He also carries a small, blue backpack. Kusi wears traditional Inca clothing: a brightly colored tunic made of woven fabric, a pair of simple, brown sandals, and a woven belt around his waist.
characters.distinctive_features: Coco has a small, round scar on his left cheek. Kusi has a feathered headband around his forehead, which is a symbol of his status in the Inca community.
characters.personality_traits: Coco's curiosity and energy are visible in his wide, bright eyes and the way he is always moving or fidgeting. Kusi's intelligence and kindness are reflected in his thoughtful, brown eyes and the gentle way he interacts with Coco.

characters.name: Kusi
characters.physical_description: Kusi is a boy of average height for his age, around 4 feet tall. He has a strong, sturdy build from helping in the fields. His skin is a warm, sun-kissed brown, and he has dark, almond-shaped eyes full of curiosity and kindness. His hair is black, thick, and straight, cut short around his ears. His face is round, with high cheekbones, a small nose, and a wide, friendly smile.
characters.clothing: Kusi wears traditional Inca clothing. He has a brightly colored tunic made of woven alpaca wool, featuring geometric patterns in red, yellow, and blue. Around his waist, he wears a woven belt with similar patterns. He has sandals made of plant fibers on his feet. On his head, he wears a small, round hat known as a montera, decorated with feathers.
characters.distinctive_features: Kusi carries a small pouch made of woven fibers, where he keeps tools and small objects he finds interesting. He also has a small stone pendant around his neck, a gift from his father.
characters.personality_traits: Kusi's helpful and friendly nature is evident in his warm, welcoming smile and bright eyes. His curiosity and intelligence are reflected in his attentive gaze and the thoughtful way he carries himself. His strength and resilience are visible in his sturdy build and the confident way he moves.

art_bible.prompt: Create a sample scene illustration in watercolor children's book illustration style for a children's book. The scene should fit a Adventure story for children. This is a reference illustration for a story titled 'the inca portal' about a school kid from today's time that travels in time to the time of the icas. The scene should showcase the visual style, colors, lighting, and artistic approach that will be used throughout the book. No text, labels, color swatches, or technical diagrams. Just a beautiful example illustration that demonstrates the artistic direction.
